Document.document: Fix Joubert's complaint that int8-sized numeric literals are mishandled on Alpha (because parser mistakenly assumes that a nonoverflow result from strtol means the value will fit into int4). A scan for other uses of strtol and strtoul found a couple other places with the same mistakeSEMICOLON fix them too. The changes are all conditional on HAVE_LONG_INT_64 to avoid complaints from compilers that think x != x is a silly test (cf. pg_atoi).

Document.document: The following patch updates the FAQ_AIX and makes C++ code work with more recent versions of the IBM C++ compiler (now called VisualAge C++). The C++ part was previously broken (g++ and xlC), thus this is zero risk. Only AIX specific parts are touched (1 Makefile.shlib line (link with $(COMPILER ) instead of $(CC) and one shell script line (parameter -C to nm to not demangle C++ symbo ls for .exp file)). I thus ask you to please apply this patch before release. With or without this patch RC1 on AIX 4.3.2 RS6000 passes "gmake check" for both the native compiler vac.C 5.0.1 and gcc 2.95.2 :-) Andreas

Document.author: pjw
Document.document: Patch to put rudimentary dependency support into pg_dump. This addresses the UDT/function order problem. - Rudimentary support for dependencies in archives. Uses dependencies to modify the OID used in sorting TOC entries. This will NOT handle multi-level dependencies, but will manage simple relationships like UDTs & their functions. - Treat OIDs with more respect (avoid using ints, use macros for conversion & comparison).

Document.author: vadim
Document.document: Check bufHdr->cntxDirty and call StartBufferIO in BufferSync() *before* acquiring shlock on buffer context. This way we should be protected against conflicts with FlushRelationBuffers. (Seems we never do excl lock and then StartBufferIO for the same buffer, so there should be no deadlock here, - but we'd better check this very soon).

Document.author: momjian
Document.document: The following patch updates the FAQ_AIX and makes C++ code work with more recent versions of the IBM C++ compiler (now called VisualAge C++). The C++ part was previously broken (g++ and xlC), thus this is zero risk. Only AIX specific parts are touched (1 Makefile.shlib line (link with $(COMPILER ) instead of $(CC) and one shell script line (parameter -C to nm to not demangle C++ symbo ls for .exp file)). I thus ask you to please apply this patch before release. With or without this patch RC1 on AIX 4.3.2 RS6000 passes "gmake check" for both the native compiler vac.C 5.0.1 and gcc 2.95.2 :-) Andreas

Document.author: tgl
Document.document: Fix Joubert's complaint that int8-sized numeric literals are mishandled on Alpha (because parser mistakenly assumes that a nonoverflow result from strtol means the value will fit into int4). A scan for other uses of strtol and strtoul found a couple other places with the same mistakeSEMICOLON fix them too. The changes are all conditional on HAVE_LONG_INT_64 to avoid complaints from compilers that think x != x is a silly test (cf. pg_atoi).
